@startuml Registration and Email Verification Flow
actor User
participant Frontend
participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
participant "Email Service" as EmailService
participant Database

User -> Frontend: Click "Create Account"
Frontend -> Frontend: Show registration form

User -> Frontend: Enter email + password
Frontend -> Frontend: Validate inputs

User -> Frontend: Click "Register"
Frontend -> BackendAPI: POST /api/v1/auth/register\n{email, password, roles: ["ROLE_USER"]}

BackendAPI -> BackendAPI: Hash password
BackendAPI -> BackendAPI: Generate 6-digit code
BackendAPI -> Database: Create user\n(IsEmailVerified=false,\nEmailVerifyCode=code)

Database -> BackendAPI: User created

BackendAPI -> EmailService: Send verification code\nto user email
EmailService -> EmailService: Generate email with code
EmailService -> User: Email arrives\nwith code (e.g., 219781)

BackendAPI -> Frontend: 201 Created\n{id, email}

Frontend -> Frontend: Show success message
Frontend -> Frontend: Navigate to login

User -> Frontend: Click link in email\nor navigate manually\nto verification page

Frontend -> Frontend: Show verify email form\nwith email pre-filled
Frontend -> Frontend: Input focus on code field

User -> Frontend: Enter verification code\n(219781)

Frontend -> BackendAPI: POST /api/v1/auth/verify-email\n{email, code}

BackendAPI -> Database: Get user by email

Database -> BackendAPI: User data

BackendAPI -> BackendAPI: Validate code matches

alt Code is valid
    BackendAPI -> Database: MarkEmailVerified(user_id)
    Database -> BackendAPI: OK
    BackendAPI -> Frontend: 200 OK\n{message: "Email verified successfully"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show success message
    Frontend -> Frontend: Navigate to login\nwith email pre-filled
    Frontend -> User: Prompt user to sign in\nwith verified account
else Code is invalid or expired
    BackendAPI -> Frontend: 400 Bad Request\n{error: "Invalid verification code"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Show error message
    Frontend -> User: Prompt to request new code\nor contact support
end

@enduml